<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=24&amp;p=33343#p33343"><![CDATA[
Chrome extensions:<br />Since many people do use google chrome, i thought I'd add a post or 2 about the everyday extensions that are OFTEN useful.<br /><br />Adblock - goes without saying..., though some ads have found a way to skirt through in recent years (and some sites go on lock-down until you disable it)<br />Fresh Start - session manager.. This extension saves all (or whichever tabs you select) as a session (actually it bookmarks everything, in a hidden folder, so it works across computers, or system reinstalls) It also has a crash recovery function, that can restore windows/tabs closed a day or 2 ago (which is very convenient when chrome occasionally looses tabs<br />Lazarus form recovery - This extension stores form data, (like really long forum post) so if you accidentally hit the back button, or close the tab. all that precious text isnt lost.<br />Clutter free - this extension ensures you dont open duplicate tabs. If your workflow is like me (with a hundred open tabs at a time) its quite easy to do.<br />PageArchiver - this extension requires a parent extension be installed on your computer, but it effectively converts webpages into single-file documents for offline viewing (and archival purposes)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Sat Jul 15, 2017 3:06 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
