X-mouse Button control<br />Freeware<br /><a href="https://www.highrez.co.uk/downloads/xmousebuttoncontrol.htm" class="postlink">https://www.highrez.co.uk/downloads/xmousebuttoncontrol.htm</a><br /><br />This handy program allows you to assign custom functions to your mouse based on what program is active, For example I have assigned win+scroll Up to increase the Volume. globally and have reconfigured the side buttons on my mouse to move between tabs in chrome. Configuration is a little tough, but once you get it configured Its quite useful.<br /><br /><br />StrokesPlus<br />Freeware<br /><a href="http://www.strokesplus.com/" class="postlink">http://www.strokesplus.com/</a><br />Adds custom mouse gestures to windows. This software is highly customizable and can do anything from sending a hotkey when a gesture is made, to opening a specific website or program. It compliments X-mouse quite well, and allows an unlimited number of functions to supplement the few buttons available on a mouse. I would strongly suggest changing the default button to either middle click, or one of the side buttons on your mouse. (right click is likely to interfere with alot of games/software)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Tue Jul 05, 2016 9:41 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
